any garden plots on campus.

521
00:29:07,541 --> 00:29:09,125
And those aren't easy to grow!

522
00:29:09,208 --> 00:29:11,666
What's your secret,
if you don't mind my asking?

523
00:29:12,541 --> 00:29:15,375
Over the course of my admittedly
brief agricultural career,

524
00:29:15,458 --> 00:29:17,000
I've discovered that
vegetables really flourish...

525
00:29:17,083 --> 00:29:18,958
So this is Eichiro Sugata,

526
00:29:19,041 --> 00:29:21,958
the head of the New
World Discovery Club.

527
00:29:22,041 --> 00:29:24,875
Everybody says he's a weirdo,
but he seems to know

528
00:29:24,958 --> 00:29:28,416
his way around a garden,
so he can't be that bad, right?

529
00:29:28,500 --> 00:29:31,625
Besides, he's
friends with Tomoki.

530
00:29:31,708 --> 00:29:34,333
I'm sure he's just fine.

531
00:29:37,625 --> 00:29:39,041
Wow!

532
00:29:39,125 --> 00:29:41,708
They've got so many
stands this year!

533
00:29:48,500 --> 00:29:50,125
Hey, Nymph!

534
00:29:52,833 --> 00:29:54,416
We got this for ya.

535
00:29:54,500 --> 00:29:55,500
You did?

536
00:29:55,583 --> 00:29:57,000
I promised I'd
get you something.

537
00:29:57,083 --> 00:29:58,875
Remember, I said if
my booth turned a profit,

538
00:29:58,958 --> 00:30:01,208
I'd buy you anything you
liked, and you like these.

539
00:30:01,291 --> 00:30:01,958
Oh.

540
00:30:02,041 --> 00:30:03,166
That's right.

541
00:30:03,250 --> 00:30:06,000
I saw, you had your
eye on these earlier.

542
00:30:06,083 --> 00:30:07,916
Plus you've been
kicking ass in the band,

543
00:30:08,000 --> 00:30:09,791
so I wanted to
give you something.

544
00:30:09,875 --> 00:30:12,333
Thanks for being awesome.

545
00:30:15,416 --> 00:30:16,333
Thanks?

546
00:30:16,416 --> 00:30:18,583
Is that what
I'm supposed to say?

547
00:30:18,666 --> 00:30:19,708
Or--

548
00:30:26,458 --> 00:30:27,583
Thank you, Master.

549
00:30:27,666 --> 00:30:29,208
Thank you so much.

550
00:30:30,958 --> 00:30:32,916
Humans are no more than bugs,

551
00:30:33,000 --> 00:30:35,375
simple creatures
who we crush underfoot.

552
00:30:35,458 --> 00:30:39,458
Even if he is nice to me,
he's still beneath me.

553
00:30:44,666 --> 00:30:45,666
It's so good.

554
00:30:45,750 --> 00:30:47,291
Isn't it?

555
00:30:52,166 --> 00:30:53,250
Way to go, Tomo!

556
00:30:53,333 --> 00:30:55,291
You made her cry!

557
00:30:55,375 --> 00:30:56,625
You little devil.

558
00:30:56,708 --> 00:30:58,291
So wicked.

559
00:30:58,375 --> 00:30:59,916
N--No, I--!

560
00:31:03,041 --> 00:31:05,916
What are you doing?

561
00:31:06,000 --> 00:31:08,166
Look Nymph.

562
00:31:08,250 --> 00:31:10,416
The sky here is so vast.

563
00:31:10,500 --> 00:31:12,791
Huh? What does
that even mean?

564
00:31:12,875 --> 00:31:14,000
--I don't get it.
--What the heck, Tomo?

565
00:31:14,083 --> 00:31:15,500
Did you do something
to upset Nymph again?

566
00:31:15,583 --> 00:31:16,333
Don't look at me!

567
00:31:16,416 --> 00:31:18,208
I didn't do anything.

568
00:31:18,916 --> 00:31:20,458
Why are you all looking at me?

569
00:31:20,541 --> 00:31:21,708
It wasn't my fault!

570
00:31:21,791 --> 00:31:23,583
This candy apple is awful!

571
00:31:23,666 --> 00:31:24,583
What are you talking about?

572
00:31:24,666 --> 00:31:25,541
You just said it was good!

573
00:31:25,625 --> 00:31:27,041
Oh shut up!

574
00:31:35,333 --> 00:31:37,916
Mikako came out here today
while they were setting up.

575
00:31:38,000 --> 00:31:40,583
Said something about
getting an event ready.

576
00:31:40,666 --> 00:31:41,666
Well, I'll be...

577
00:31:41,750 --> 00:31:43,416
You grew all
this yourself, dearie?

578
00:31:43,500 --> 00:31:44,916
Uh-huh!

579
00:31:45,000 --> 00:31:46,000
Tell you what.

580
00:31:46,083 --> 00:31:47,708
I'll take one of
them daikon radishes.

581
00:31:47,791 --> 00:31:48,875
Great!

582
00:31:49,208 --> 00:31:51,166
Thank you very much, ma'am!

583
00:31:54,333 --> 00:31:55,541
Huh?

584
00:32:10,375 --> 00:32:11,416
He's groping her!

585
00:32:11,500 --> 00:32:13,083
Oh, the humanity!

586
00:32:13,166 --> 00:32:15,500
Pants is groping Makiko!

587
00:32:15,583 --> 00:32:17,750
I-- I give up!

588
00:32:23,583 --> 00:32:24,750
No way!

589
00:32:24,833 --> 00:32:26,708
He's already in a tight spot!

590
00:32:26,791 --> 00:32:29,125
The man's face is being crushed!

591
00:32:29,208 --> 00:32:31,458
This does not look good!

592
00:32:31,541 --> 00:32:33,958
Flying body press!

593
00:32:38,416 --> 00:32:41,625
She's reaching--oh!
To catch him mid-air-- Oh!

594
00:32:41,708 --> 00:32:45,500
and performs an
Argentine Backbreaker!

595
00:32:51,500 --> 00:32:52,625
--and here's your candy apple.

596
00:32:52,708 --> 00:32:54,416
I hope you like it!

597
00:32:54,500 --> 00:32:56,000
Thanks a lot!

598
00:32:58,583 --> 00:33:00,375
Nymph is so adorable.

599
00:33:00,458 --> 00:33:02,750
She reminds me of a doll.

600
00:33:07,208 --> 00:33:09,166
She's not the only one.

601
00:33:09,250 --> 00:33:11,500
They're all adorable.

602
00:33:11,583 --> 00:33:15,875
Why would Tomoki notice
me with them around?

603
00:33:16,208 --> 00:33:17,833
I hope he does, though.

604
00:33:17,916 --> 00:33:19,958
I really do.

605
00:33:20,875 --> 00:33:22,541
Man, a lot happened
in one night,

606
00:33:22,625 --> 00:33:25,000
but the festival
was fun, wasn't it?

607
00:33:25,083 --> 00:33:26,791
Are you sure that's
all you wanted?

608
00:33:26,875 --> 00:33:30,500
I said I'd get you anything,
and I do keep my promises.

609
00:33:31,416 --> 00:33:33,250
'Cause the last time
you had a candy apple

610
00:33:33,333 --> 00:33:35,416
you said they
were gross tasting.

611
00:33:36,083 --> 00:33:37,541
You remember that?

612
00:33:37,625 --> 00:33:40,416
Course. You cried over
it like a baby.

613
00:33:42,125 --> 00:33:44,208
But I do like them.

614
00:33:45,083 --> 00:33:46,750
Candy apples.

615
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:50,583
I like them a lot.

616
00:33:53,708 --> 00:33:55,833
Hey Tomoki, aren't you
going to have one, too?

617
00:33:55,916 --> 00:34:00,000
Nah, I already had a bunch of
takoyaki and other junk today.

618
00:34:00,083 --> 00:34:01,708
You don't eat a lot
of sweets, do you?

619
00:34:01,791 --> 00:34:03,333
Not really.

620
00:34:06,583 --> 00:34:08,208
First snow of the year!

621
00:34:08,958 --> 00:34:13,500
Perfect day to
do absolutely nothing.

622
00:34:14,041 --> 00:34:15,708
War is hell!

623
00:34:15,791 --> 00:34:19,291
All students, report to the
P.E. field immediately!

624
00:34:19,375 --> 00:34:22,125
Two teams--boys on one,
girls on the other!

625
00:34:22,208 --> 00:34:23,500
We're going to
duke it out like our

626
00:34:23,583 --> 00:34:27,666
ancestors always did
with snowballs!

627
00:34:29,333 --> 00:34:32,416
Just like that, all of our
classes were cancelled.

628
00:34:32,500 --> 00:34:36,708
Everyone headed outside for the
most epic snowball fight ever!

629
00:34:40,583 --> 00:34:41,333
Your Lordship!

630
00:34:41,416 --> 00:34:43,000
What's it gonna be?

631
00:34:45,166 --> 00:34:47,708
The enemy is at Honnoji!

632
00:34:59,708 --> 00:35:01,708
Ready!
Fire!

633
00:35:24,208 --> 00:35:26,416
So uh-- Could you do me a favor?

634
00:35:26,500 --> 00:35:27,500
Well that depends.

635
00:35:27,583 --> 00:35:29,250
What do you want?

636
00:35:43,541 --> 00:35:45,458
This is paradise.

637
00:35:45,541 --> 00:35:49,458
I haven't relaxed in a hot
spring like this in forever!

638
00:36:22,583 --> 00:36:25,125
Hiyori!
You really called it!

639
00:36:25,208 --> 00:36:26,791
This place is amazing!

640
00:36:27,291 --> 00:36:28,875
I found it recently.

641
00:36:28,958 --> 00:36:31,458
I'm just glad you're
having a good time.

642
00:36:32,416 --> 00:36:34,041
It's gonna eat me!

643
00:36:34,125 --> 00:36:35,625
Why'd I even bother
coming out here, huh?

644
00:36:35,708 --> 00:36:36,875
Look over there.

645
00:36:36,958 --> 00:36:39,291
It's Tomoki, that
pervert from Class C.

646
00:36:39,375 --> 00:36:41,625
He's always getting in
some kind of trouble!

647
00:36:41,708 --> 00:36:43,041
What a pain in the ass!

648
00:36:43,125 --> 00:36:44,125
Oh?

649
00:36:44,208 --> 00:36:46,291
But he seems like
such a fun guy.

650
00:36:46,375 --> 00:36:49,500
Whenever I see him, I just
know it'll be a good day.

651
00:36:49,583 --> 00:36:52,708
I guess-- I, uh-- y'know.

652
00:36:52,791 --> 00:36:54,250
I like him.

653
00:36:54,875 --> 00:36:57,333
I've watched the nature channel!
I know what happens next!

654
00:36:57,416 --> 00:37:00,333
This is why I said
fishing is bullshit, man!

655
00:37:00,416 --> 00:37:02,458
Whenever Tomoki was around.

656
00:37:02,541 --> 00:37:05,875
I just sort of forgot
about everything else.

657
00:37:09,416 --> 00:37:10,416
Yeah.

658
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:12,666
I couldn't deny it anymore.

659
00:37:12,750 --> 00:37:15,458
I had really fallen for him.

660
00:37:21,083 --> 00:37:22,458
Air!

661
00:37:24,083 --> 00:37:26,500
Uh, what are you
doing down there?

662
00:37:26,583 --> 00:37:28,708
I heard that veggies get
their food from the dirt,

663
00:37:28,791 --> 00:37:30,791
so I figured I'd give it a shot!

664
00:37:30,875 --> 00:37:32,208
Huh?

665
00:37:33,500 --> 00:37:35,000
You know, if you're that hungry

666
00:37:35,083 --> 00:37:37,291
I could just give you
some vegetables.

667
00:37:37,375 --> 00:37:38,125
Yeah?

668
00:37:38,208 --> 00:37:38,958
Like for free?

669
00:37:39,041 --> 00:37:40,875
Score!

670
00:37:48,458 --> 00:37:50,833
These cucumbers are delish!

671
00:37:53,333 --> 00:37:55,833
Whatcha gonna do with
all these veggies, huh?

672
00:37:55,916 --> 00:37:57,208
Well, I was thinking
of giving them to the

673
00:37:57,291 --> 00:37:59,958
animals at school we
keep as class pets.

674
00:38:00,041 --> 00:38:02,625
Mikako's always being so nice
to me, I figured the least

675
00:38:02,708 --> 00:38:05,166
I could do was help
her out with their food.

676
00:38:05,250 --> 00:38:06,458
Cool!

677
00:38:06,541 --> 00:38:08,291
She's my sensei!

678
00:38:11,083 --> 00:38:14,375
It's like an
all-you-can-eat buffet!

679
00:38:21,833 --> 00:38:22,916
What's all the fuss about?

680
00:38:23,000 --> 00:38:25,000
Dude, let's go check it out.

681
00:38:35,833 --> 00:38:37,833
Oh, Astraea, no.

682
00:38:44,250 --> 00:38:48,166
I give it my all, but my
cooking is so plain.

683
00:38:48,250 --> 00:38:50,708
I can't offer these
cookies to Tomoki.

684
00:38:50,791 --> 00:38:52,791
I mean, look at them.

685
00:38:54,625 --> 00:38:56,291
Just look at 'em!

686
00:38:56,375 --> 00:38:57,208
Dig in.

687
00:38:57,291 --> 00:38:59,000
As many as you'd like!

688
00:39:00,083 --> 00:39:00,833
Thanks!

689
00:39:00,916 --> 00:39:01,583
Ikaros?
Care for a cookie?

690
00:39:01,666 --> 00:39:03,833
This smells like tasty!

691
00:39:07,375 --> 00:39:08,541
I'm in heaven!

692
00:39:08,625 --> 00:39:10,000
They're delicious.

693
00:39:10,333 --> 00:39:11,833
I'm so glad.

694
00:39:11,916 --> 00:39:12,958
Hey, I know!

695
00:39:13,041 --> 00:39:14,833
Since you like
watermelons so much,

696
00:39:14,916 --> 00:39:17,000
why don't you have
Hiyori teach you about 'em?

697
00:39:17,083 --> 00:39:18,541
Her melons are radical!

698
00:39:18,625 --> 00:39:19,500
Like for real!

699
00:39:19,583 --> 00:39:20,666
Huh?

700
00:39:20,750 --> 00:39:21,750
You said there was
stuff about growing 'em

701
00:39:21,833 --> 00:39:23,125
that you still
didn't know, right?

702
00:39:23,208 --> 00:39:25,708
Well, this chick is like
the produce whisperer,

703
00:39:25,791 --> 00:39:27,416
so problem solved!

704
00:39:29,208 --> 00:39:31,791
If I can be of use,
I'd love to help.

705
00:39:31,875 --> 00:39:33,625
Change a few things in
your garden and you'll be

706
00:39:33,708 --> 00:39:35,875
growing tons of
watermelons in no time!

707
00:39:35,958 --> 00:39:37,333
Trust me!

708
00:39:37,416 --> 00:39:41,416
Watermelons by the ton?

709
00:39:43,083 --> 00:39:44,166
Yes, please.

710
00:39:44,250 --> 00:39:46,000
I would like that a lot.

711
00:39:46,083 --> 00:39:46,875
Hey!

712
00:39:46,958 --> 00:39:48,208
What's up?

713
00:39:48,291 --> 00:39:50,416
I smelled cookies and
thought I'd check it out!

714
00:39:52,333 --> 00:39:53,083
Uh!

715
00:39:53,166 --> 00:39:54,375
Yeah have a cookie!

716
00:39:54,458 --> 00:39:55,250
Oh no!

717
00:39:55,333 --> 00:39:57,041
I don't have any cookies left!

718
00:39:57,125 --> 00:39:57,916
They're gone!

719
00:39:58,000 --> 00:39:59,583
I'm so sorry!

720
00:40:00,125 --> 00:40:01,083
Hey, it's fine.

721
00:40:01,166 --> 00:40:03,041
I'm sure they were great.

722
00:40:06,375 --> 00:40:08,041
See ya later!

723
00:40:13,666 --> 00:40:15,791
Tomoki looked at me.

724
00:40:15,875 --> 00:40:17,625
He spoke to me.

725
00:40:17,708 --> 00:40:20,208
He even smiled.

726
00:40:22,166 --> 00:40:24,833
From that moment on,
something inside my

727
00:40:24,916 --> 00:40:27,708
heart began to blossom and grow.

728
00:40:27,791 --> 00:40:30,916
Maybe Tomoki and I
could become friends.

729
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:33,791
Maybe close friends
or even more.

730
00:40:33,875 --> 00:40:36,500
My wish set down
roots in my heart and

731
00:40:36,583 --> 00:40:40,208
it grew little by little as
I watched Tomoki.

732
00:40:40,291 --> 00:40:45,250
I watered it with hope
and he was its sunshine.

733
00:41:14,958 --> 00:41:16,208
Oh, cool.

734
00:41:16,291 --> 00:41:18,125
The actress on Barnyard
Sonata is getting married.

735
00:41:18,208 --> 00:41:20,083
Remind me to
tell Nymph about this.

736
00:41:20,166 --> 00:41:22,166
Sohara, I have a question.

737
00:41:22,250 --> 00:41:23,541
Sure, what is it?

738
00:41:23,625 --> 00:41:26,333
When someone proposes to you,

739
00:41:26,416 --> 00:41:28,333
is marriage what
happens afterwards?

740
00:41:28,416 --> 00:41:29,125
Yep.

741
00:41:29,208 --> 00:41:30,416
Check it out.

742
00:41:30,500 --> 00:41:31,666
After the proposal,
you have a wedding and you

743
00:41:31,750 --> 00:41:34,041
get to wear a beautiful
dress like this one.

744
00:41:34,125 --> 00:41:36,166
Isn't it gorgeous?

745
00:41:36,250 --> 00:41:38,541
A proposal, then a wedding.

746
00:41:40,791 --> 00:41:43,041
What are you talking about?

747
00:41:43,125 --> 00:41:44,166
Nothing.

748
00:41:44,250 --> 00:41:46,333
Maybe the heat's
making you lightheaded.

749
00:41:46,416 --> 00:41:48,500
I know! We should
go get some ice cream.

750
00:41:48,583 --> 00:41:51,166
That's the best thing to
do when it's hot outside.

751
00:41:51,250 --> 00:41:52,833
Yeah!

752
00:41:54,916 --> 00:41:57,166
Hiyori!
What's up?

753
00:41:59,458 --> 00:42:01,333
Sohara and Ikaros.

754
00:42:01,416 --> 00:42:03,375
Uh, good afternoon.

755
00:42:03,458 --> 00:42:06,291
If you're not busy, we were
about to go get some ice cream.

756
00:42:06,375 --> 00:42:07,666
You wanna come with?

757
00:42:07,750 --> 00:42:08,500
Huh?

758
00:42:08,583 --> 00:42:09,625
Uh yeah.

759
00:42:09,708 --> 00:42:11,375
Thanks.

760
00:42:14,291 --> 00:42:16,083
Y'know, I'm glad
we're finally getting

761
00:42:16,166 --> 00:42:18,250
a chance to hang out for once.

762
00:42:18,333 --> 00:42:21,000
Yeah, I'm glad also.

763
00:42:21,083 --> 00:42:23,000
I've been seeing a
lot of you and

764
00:42:23,083 --> 00:42:25,083
your friends around
town this year.

765
00:42:25,166 --> 00:42:26,166
Honestly?

766
00:42:26,250 --> 00:42:28,375
I'm jealous of how
you all get along!

767
00:42:28,458 --> 00:42:30,166
You've been watching us?

768
00:42:30,250 --> 00:42:33,500
Whenever you're all together,
you have a lot of fun.

769
00:42:33,583 --> 00:42:35,666
Like just the other day,
when you ate curry

770
00:42:35,750 --> 00:42:37,333
in the woods
down by the stream.

771
00:42:37,416 --> 00:42:38,416
You were there?

772
00:42:38,500 --> 00:42:40,458
Aw, how come you
didn't say something?

773
00:42:40,541 --> 00:42:43,833
Because I'm not a member of
the New World Discovery Club.

774
00:42:43,916 --> 00:42:45,541
Makes no difference to me!

775
00:42:45,625 --> 00:42:47,625
In fact, I betcha Tomoki
would've hollered for you

776
00:42:47,708 --> 00:42:49,916
to come over and
fill up a plate.

777
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:53,333
You-- you really think so?

778
00:42:53,416 --> 00:42:54,708
Course I do.

779
00:42:54,791 --> 00:42:57,166
Tomo's always
being nice like that.

780
00:42:57,250 --> 00:42:59,833
I mean, that's basically
what he did with Astraea.

781
00:42:59,916 --> 00:43:02,333
Man, that girl can
really pack it away.

782
00:43:03,125 --> 00:43:07,166
I-- I knew that it was
a long-shot, but--

783
00:43:15,166 --> 00:43:19,958
If I wanted him to know
I existed, I had to be brave.

784
00:43:20,750 --> 00:43:25,625
So the very next day, I marched
