1293
01:11:56,833 --> 01:11:58,708
I'm unclaimed.

1294
01:11:58,791 --> 01:12:00,125
Nymph, I--

1295
01:12:00,208 --> 01:12:01,666
Okay, okay.

1296
01:12:01,750 --> 01:12:03,500
Even though he's just gonna
forget everything

1297
01:12:03,583 --> 01:12:05,250
about her tomorrow anyhow,

1298
01:12:05,333 --> 01:12:08,750
I guess I shouldn't
have lied to him like that.

1299
01:12:09,500 --> 01:12:11,416
Now you've got
me feeling all guilty!

1300
01:12:11,500 --> 01:12:15,500
Tell you what--I'll go and make
it up to him right away, okay?

1301
01:12:25,458 --> 01:12:27,083
What the hell do you
think you're doing, Nymph?

1302
01:12:27,166 --> 01:12:28,583
What's wrong, Tomoki?

1303
01:12:28,666 --> 01:12:30,500
I thought you liked this outfit.

1304
01:12:30,583 --> 01:12:31,583
Like it?

1305
01:12:31,666 --> 01:12:33,416
You damn near gave
me a heart attack!

1306
01:12:33,500 --> 01:12:34,750
Come to bed.

1307
01:12:34,833 --> 01:12:35,833
Huh?

1308
01:12:35,916 --> 01:12:38,541
I came here to snuggle up.

1309
01:12:39,000 --> 01:12:41,166
So come back.

1310
01:12:46,291 --> 01:12:48,166
Whatever you say.

1311
01:12:55,875 --> 01:12:58,666
Hey, Tomoki.

1312
01:12:58,750 --> 01:12:59,708
That's my name.

1313
01:12:59,791 --> 01:13:02,208
Remember, how you
told me that one

1314
01:13:02,291 --> 01:13:06,291
time that you would
become my master?

1315
01:13:08,375 --> 01:13:13,750
I'm ready to imprint,
if you meant it.

1316
01:13:16,291 --> 01:13:17,583
Don't do it.

1317
01:13:17,666 --> 01:13:19,416
At the end of the
day, the only one you

1318
01:13:19,500 --> 01:13:22,250
should have to
answer to is yourself.

1319
01:13:22,875 --> 01:13:25,000
That goes for
you and Ikaros both.

1320
01:13:25,083 --> 01:13:26,708
And even Astraea.

1321
01:13:26,791 --> 01:13:28,291
What kind of life
would you have if you

1322
01:13:28,375 --> 01:13:31,125
spend it following
someone's orders?

1323
01:13:31,208 --> 01:13:34,166
You deserve way better.

1324
01:13:35,208 --> 01:13:37,416
Freedom is pretty bitchin',

1325
01:13:37,500 --> 01:13:40,500
and I want you to
have that, you know?

1326
01:13:40,958 --> 01:13:43,500
Having masters isn't all bad.

1327
01:13:43,583 --> 01:13:47,375
Life's complicated when you have
to figure stuff out on your own.

1328
01:13:47,458 --> 01:13:49,083
Look, it's not like I want you

1329
01:13:49,166 --> 01:13:51,916
to be my master
because I'm an Angeloid.

1330
01:13:52,000 --> 01:13:54,000
It's 'cause-- 

1331
01:13:54,083 --> 01:13:57,208
'Cause I think you're amazing!

1332
01:13:57,291 --> 01:13:59,166
Tomoki, I think that I'm in l--

1333
01:13:59,833 --> 01:14:01,250
Tomoki?

1334
01:14:01,333 --> 01:14:03,000
What the hell!

1335
01:14:03,083 --> 01:14:04,708
Tomoki!

1336
01:14:05,916 --> 01:14:07,916
That's the pain of
memories being zapped

1337
01:14:08,000 --> 01:14:10,458
out of your mind by the Synapse.

1338
01:14:11,166 --> 01:14:14,625
By tomorrow, Hiyori will
never have existed!

1339
01:14:26,375 --> 01:14:27,125
Huh?

1340
01:14:27,208 --> 01:14:28,583
What'd you say her name was?

1341
01:14:28,666 --> 01:14:29,541
It's Hiyori!

1342
01:14:29,625 --> 01:14:30,833
Hiyori Kazane!

1343
01:14:30,916 --> 01:14:32,333
Geez.

1344
01:14:32,791 --> 01:14:34,833
All that porn's rotted
your brain, Tomo.

1345
01:14:34,916 --> 01:14:36,333
We don't have any new members.

1346
01:14:36,416 --> 01:14:37,625
I think I'd have noticed.

1347
01:14:37,708 --> 01:14:39,333
I've never heard that name.

1348
01:14:39,416 --> 01:14:42,458
And believe me,
I have dirt on everybody.

1349
01:14:42,541 --> 01:14:44,791
Are you sure that this
wasn't just another dream?

1350
01:14:44,875 --> 01:14:46,333
Oh, come on!

1351
01:14:46,416 --> 01:14:48,708
She bumped us into a higher
bracket for the club budget.

1352
01:14:48,791 --> 01:14:50,666
You practically drooled on her!

1353
01:14:50,750 --> 01:14:52,125
Wait, I got it!

1354
01:14:52,208 --> 01:14:53,458
Remember when
you took all of those

1355
01:14:53,541 --> 01:14:56,000
pictures of us doing like,
club stuff, Sohara?

1356
01:14:56,083 --> 01:14:58,833
Yeah--the album's
right over here.

1357
01:15:05,625 --> 01:15:06,833
What the hell?

1358
01:15:06,916 --> 01:15:08,666
She's gone.

1359
01:15:10,708 --> 01:15:13,333
Something fishy's going on here!

1360
01:15:14,250 --> 01:15:16,500
Uh, Tomo, where're you going?

1361
01:15:24,375 --> 01:15:25,666
I'm awake!

1362
01:15:25,750 --> 01:15:26,666
No, please!

1363
01:15:26,750 --> 01:15:28,291
Send me back into the dream!

1364
01:15:28,375 --> 01:15:29,375
I beg of you!

1365
01:15:29,458 --> 01:15:32,041
You wanted your dream,
and you had it.

1366
01:15:32,125 --> 01:15:36,291
Mewling for do-overs after
the fact is just ungrateful.

1367
01:15:37,333 --> 01:15:40,875
Your little charade
has come to a messy end.

1368
01:15:40,958 --> 01:15:43,333
You've been purged
from their memories.

1369
01:15:43,416 --> 01:15:45,708
You're nothing to them.

1370
01:15:53,833 --> 01:15:56,625
Well, it appears
you're not entirely

1371
01:15:56,708 --> 01:15:59,500
forgettable to one
of those insects.

1372
01:16:03,375 --> 01:16:05,166
Tomoki, of course.

1373
01:16:07,000 --> 01:16:09,166
You can see him again, you know.

1374
01:16:09,250 --> 01:16:13,625
So long as you don't mind
making certain sacrifices.

1375
01:16:21,083 --> 01:16:23,791
Hiyori, where are you?

1376
01:16:38,875 --> 01:16:40,583
Damn it all, Hiyori!

1377
01:16:40,666 --> 01:16:44,250
Where did you go?

1378
01:17:00,583 --> 01:17:02,250
Look at you.

1379
01:17:03,791 --> 01:17:04,916
You knew.

1380
01:17:05,000 --> 01:17:07,166
You knew that she was real.

1381
01:17:07,250 --> 01:17:08,958
Master, we thought that--

1382
01:17:09,041 --> 01:17:10,791
No-- you can't!

1383
01:17:11,208 --> 01:17:14,583
Tell the truth right now!

1384
01:17:15,250 --> 01:17:16,791
She wanted to
tell you the truth!

1385
01:17:16,875 --> 01:17:18,375
Don't blame her--blame me!

1386
01:17:18,458 --> 01:17:21,666
It's just once a human learns
the truth about this stuff,

1387
01:17:21,750 --> 01:17:24,041
their mind can't
be wiped anymore!

1388
01:17:24,125 --> 01:17:26,958
That's why you were
never supposed to find out!

1389
01:17:27,041 --> 01:17:27,958
About what?

1390
01:17:28,041 --> 01:17:29,208
Just say it!

1391
01:17:29,291 --> 01:17:31,833
Hiyori never really
did exist in this world,

1392
01:17:31,916 --> 01:17:34,666
but she's not the only one!

1393
01:17:38,541 --> 01:17:40,041
--Tomoki!
--Master!

1394
01:17:46,500 --> 01:17:50,125
How is it possible Master's
memories were not erased?

1395
01:17:50,208 --> 01:17:51,416
I don't know.

1396
01:17:51,500 --> 01:17:53,416
But the longer he retains
them, the worse off

1397
01:17:53,500 --> 01:17:55,708
he's going to be
in the long run.

1398
01:17:55,791 --> 01:17:56,958
What's that even mean?

1399
01:17:57,041 --> 01:17:59,291
Tomoki remembers all
the stuff about Hiyori

1400
01:17:59,375 --> 01:18:01,541
that the Synapse took
from everyone else.

1401
01:18:01,625 --> 01:18:04,958
After a while, the strain of
it's gonna break him down.

1402
01:18:05,625 --> 01:18:07,791
It's "when," not "if".

1403
01:18:07,875 --> 01:18:10,708
How come a dummy
like him can't forget?

1404
01:18:12,041 --> 01:18:14,000
I forget all the time.

1405
01:18:14,083 --> 01:18:17,500
There must be
something we can do.

1406
01:18:20,125 --> 01:18:21,791
What the--?

1407
01:18:24,583 --> 01:18:25,750
What did you pick up?

1408
01:18:25,833 --> 01:18:29,250
I dunno, but whatever
it is, it can't be good!

1409
01:18:40,458 --> 01:18:42,000
You're kidding me!

1410
01:19:02,041 --> 01:19:03,500
Oh, thank goodness.

1411
01:19:03,583 --> 01:19:06,458
I made it back
to my beloved home.

1412
01:19:07,458 --> 01:19:09,750
Sorami City!

1413
01:19:12,375 --> 01:19:14,208
It's Hiyori.

1414
01:19:21,500 --> 01:19:23,083
Hiyori!

1415
01:19:36,416 --> 01:19:40,958
She's become an Angeloid?

1416
01:19:43,833 --> 01:19:46,625
Engaging: Kairos.

1417
01:19:49,166 --> 01:19:50,708
Oh, no!

1418
01:19:50,791 --> 01:19:51,958
You monster!

1419
01:19:52,041 --> 01:19:54,958
How could you bring
her back as an Angeloid?

1420
01:19:55,416 --> 01:19:57,291
Are you insane?

1421
01:19:57,375 --> 01:19:59,291
Why should you care either way?

1422
01:19:59,375 --> 01:20:02,875
She was a Synapsian, but she
turned her back on the glory of

1423
01:20:02,958 --> 01:20:04,916
this world in
favor of that insect

1424
01:20:05,000 --> 01:20:07,083
and that grimy little dung-heap.

1425
01:20:07,166 --> 01:20:12,541
So I sent her back, as the
destroyer of all she holds dear.

1426
01:20:12,916 --> 01:20:14,750
I've returned, Tomoki.

1427
01:20:14,833 --> 01:20:16,666
What are you waiting for, Zeta?

1428
01:20:16,750 --> 01:20:20,166
It's time to make
your wish come true!

1429
01:20:21,208 --> 01:20:21,833
Hiyori!

1430
01:20:21,916 --> 01:20:22,583
Stop!

1431
01:20:22,666 --> 01:20:23,375
Hiyori!

1432
01:20:23,458 --> 01:20:25,125
Crap-cakes!

1433
01:20:27,166 --> 01:20:28,916
Hey, Ikaros?

1434
01:20:54,500 --> 01:20:55,791
Stop attacking us, Hiyori!

1435
01:20:55,875 --> 01:20:56,958
We're your friends!

1436
01:20:57,041 --> 01:20:59,791
The lights are on,
but Hiyori ain't home!

1437
01:20:59,875 --> 01:21:01,958
Nicely done, Zeta!

1438
01:21:02,458 --> 01:21:04,875
Now annihilate every
human you can find!

1439
01:21:04,958 --> 01:21:08,500
Where are you
hiding, Tomoki dear?

1440
01:21:20,666 --> 01:21:22,625
We have to stop her, and quick!

1441
01:21:22,708 --> 01:21:25,208
The direction she's going'll
take her straight into town!

1442
01:21:25,291 --> 01:21:26,458
We asked nice!

1443
01:21:26,541 --> 01:21:27,750
So what's plan B?

1444
01:21:27,833 --> 01:21:30,958
We'll have to take Hiyori out.

1445
01:21:31,833 --> 01:21:35,291
A master's orders are absolute--
we know that better than anyone!

1446
01:21:35,375 --> 01:21:38,291
If we let her go, she's won't
stop 'til she kills Tomoki!

1447
01:21:38,375 --> 01:21:39,416
Yeah, but--!

1448
01:21:39,500 --> 01:21:40,875
Don't worry, Astraea.

1449
01:21:40,958 --> 01:21:41,958
I'll do it.

1450
01:21:42,041 --> 01:21:44,250
She's not sporting
any serious armor.

1451
01:21:44,333 --> 01:21:47,958
One blast of my Paradise
Song should be enough!

1452
01:21:48,791 --> 01:21:50,500
I'm sorry.

1453
01:21:50,583 --> 01:21:51,625
No--you mustn't!

1454
01:21:51,708 --> 01:21:53,000
What the hell?

1455
01:21:53,083 --> 01:21:56,083
If I let you destroy Hiyori,
it will sadden Master!

1456
01:21:58,250 --> 01:22:00,833
Tomoki has no idea what
we're up against, Alpha!

1457
01:22:00,916 --> 01:22:03,125
If we act now,
no one else gets hurt!

1458
01:22:03,208 --> 01:22:04,083
I'm not sure.

1459
01:22:04,166 --> 01:22:06,125
Why'd they make me so stupid?

1460
01:22:06,208 --> 01:22:08,458
It's like "one plus one"
all over again!

1461
01:22:08,541 --> 01:22:09,833
Move.

1462
01:22:14,750 --> 01:22:16,958
I have to do this.

1463
01:22:21,291 --> 01:22:22,291
Take her out.

1464
01:22:22,375 --> 01:22:25,375
One shout and it's done.

1465
01:22:26,166 --> 01:22:28,291
Quick and painless!

1466
01:22:31,458 --> 01:22:33,041
Don't do it, Nymph.

1467
01:22:33,125 --> 01:22:35,333
The one you're
gonna hurt is you.

1468
01:22:36,833 --> 01:22:39,083
I can't do it.

1469
01:22:42,625 --> 01:22:43,708
Hiyori!

1470
01:22:43,791 --> 01:22:45,916
I swear I'm gonna help you!

1471
01:22:46,000 --> 01:22:48,375
Damn you, Tomoki Sakurai!

1472
01:22:48,458 --> 01:22:50,083
What are you waiting for, Zeta?

1473
01:22:50,166 --> 01:22:52,000
Destroy him!

1474
01:22:52,333 --> 01:22:53,791
Aegis-L!

1475
01:22:56,583 --> 01:22:57,500
Tomoki!
Over here!

1476
01:22:57,583 --> 01:22:59,000
Sugata?

1477
01:23:00,166 --> 01:23:02,083
Keep her busy long as you can!

1478
01:23:02,166 --> 01:23:03,125
Ikaros!

1479
01:23:03,208 --> 01:23:04,625
What happens
if we attack all that

1480
01:23:04,708 --> 01:23:06,791
mechanical junk
floating behind her?

1481
01:23:07,333 --> 01:23:09,500
I mean, if we can
bust up all that crap,

1482
01:23:09,583 --> 01:23:11,541
do you think Hiyori'll
go back to normal?

1483
01:23:11,625 --> 01:23:14,083
I don't know,
but it's worth a try.

1484
01:23:14,166 --> 01:23:16,166
I'll hack her system
to immobilize her.

1485
01:23:16,250 --> 01:23:19,125
While I'm doing that, I need you
two to destroy that machinery!

1486
01:23:19,208 --> 01:23:20,208
Okay?

1487
01:23:20,291 --> 01:23:21,625
Go!

1488
01:23:31,583 --> 01:23:33,708
All right!
Now!

1489
01:23:35,041 --> 01:23:36,583
Hack initiated!

1490
01:23:37,625 --> 01:23:39,041
Nymph!
What's wrong?

1491
01:23:39,125 --> 01:23:41,333
Hiyori executed a counter-hack!

1492
01:23:41,875 --> 01:23:44,791
You rejects are so
easy to outsmart.

1493
01:23:44,875 --> 01:23:47,125
I equipped this one with
top-notch electronics

1494
01:23:47,208 --> 01:23:49,458
for just such an occasion.

1495
01:23:55,041 --> 01:23:56,583
Chrysaor!

1496
01:23:56,666 --> 01:23:58,625
You leave her alone!

1497
01:23:58,708 --> 01:24:00,125
Kairos.

1498
01:24:04,208 --> 01:24:05,916
I just got rewound!

1499
01:24:06,833 --> 01:24:08,583
Kairos.

1500
01:24:14,875 --> 01:24:16,291
Nymph!

1501
01:24:16,375 --> 01:24:20,250
So, you like to get cute with
time-manipulation, do ya?

1502
01:24:21,291 --> 01:24:24,541
Hacking field, maximum range!

1503
01:24:27,125 --> 01:24:28,291
Now, Delta!

1504
01:24:28,375 --> 01:24:30,416
Try rushing her again--
and this time, floor it!

1505
01:24:30,500 --> 01:24:31,500
Okay!

1506
01:24:31,583 --> 01:24:32,875
Alpha!
Fire!

1507
01:24:32,958 --> 01:24:34,583
If I must!

1508
01:24:48,333 --> 01:24:50,583
Take that stuff!

1509
01:24:53,875 --> 01:24:55,541
Oh, no.

1510
01:24:56,541 --> 01:24:57,833
It's no use!

1511
01:24:57,916 --> 01:25:00,583
She's an Angeloid now,
and there's no undoing that!

1512
01:25:00,666 --> 01:25:03,875
She chose this fate, forsaking
her very nature for the chance

1513
01:25:03,958 --> 01:25:08,166
to see Tomoki Sakurai again--
and now she'll kill him!

1514
01:25:08,250 --> 01:25:10,000
My master!

1515
01:25:10,958 --> 01:25:12,875
That sound.
It can't be!

1516
01:25:12,958 --> 01:25:14,833
That's her countdown timer!

1517
01:25:15,166 --> 01:25:18,000
If you tamper with time and
space too much all at once,

1518
01:25:18,083 --> 01:25:22,291
the temporal-spatio paradox
releases a massive energy burst!

1519
01:25:22,750 --> 01:25:23,750
That's smart-people talk for

1520
01:25:23,833 --> 01:25:25,666
"She's gonna blow
up the town," huh?

1521
01:25:25,750 --> 01:25:27,041
It is!

1522
01:25:27,125 --> 01:25:28,958
There's gotta be something
you can do to stop her!

1523
01:25:29,041 --> 01:25:31,416
Can't you just break
off the ticking part?

1524
01:25:31,500 --> 01:25:34,000
Maybe I can bypass her
command to self-destruct.

1525
01:25:34,083 --> 01:25:35,083
But if I fail--

1526
01:25:35,166 --> 01:25:36,583
Then what'll happen?

1527
01:25:36,666 --> 01:25:40,500
Hiyori and everything around
her will be annihilated.

1528
01:25:40,583 --> 01:25:43,375
I know I have to do it,
but it's not the bad ones'

1529
01:25:43,458 --> 01:25:45,333
fault they didn't work out.

1530
01:25:45,416 --> 01:25:48,291
Extend Aegis around
myself and Hiyori!

1531
01:25:48,375 --> 01:25:49,541
Of course!

1532
01:25:49,625 --> 01:25:51,125
Aegis is strong enough
to contain the blast!

1533
01:25:51,208 --> 01:25:53,375
The explosion won't
even reach Sorami!

1534
01:25:53,458 --> 01:25:55,375
Good thinking, Ikaros!

1535
01:25:58,833 --> 01:26:01,041
Huh?
How come she's inside it?

1536
01:26:01,125 --> 01:26:02,291
Get out of there, Alpha!

1537
01:26:02,375 --> 01:26:04,000
If she goes off while
you're both inside,

1538
01:26:04,083 --> 01:26:06,458
you'll be vaporized, too!

1539
01:26:06,541 --> 01:26:08,083
You and I are the same.

1540
01:26:08,166 --> 01:26:10,250
We were given powers
we never asked for,

1541
01:26:10,333 --> 01:26:12,375
and ordered to hurt people.

1542
01:26:13,166 --> 01:26:16,333
Our reactors ache
for the same person.

1543
01:26:17,291 --> 01:26:18,333
Hiyori.

1544
01:26:18,416 --> 01:26:20,541
So you understand
why I feel that way?

1545
01:26:20,625 --> 01:26:23,583
Sure, they're plants but I
betcha they have feelings, too!

1546
01:26:23,666 --> 01:26:26,458
Poor little watermelon,
all alone!

1547
01:26:28,541 --> 01:26:30,958
You do not have to be alone.

1548
01:26:31,833 --> 01:26:33,958
I will stay with you...

1549
01:26:34,416 --> 01:26:36,458
To the very end.

1550
01:26:38,000 --> 01:26:40,250
Forgive me, Master.

1551
01:26:40,333 --> 01:26:42,791
I cannot let
Hiyori perish alone.

1552
01:26:42,875 --> 01:26:44,416
Ikaros!

1553
01:26:44,500 --> 01:26:46,541
I ordered you not to die!

1554
01:26:46,625 --> 01:26:47,708
Tomoki?

1555
01:26:47,791 --> 01:26:49,666
Man, is he dumb!

1556
01:26:51,083 --> 01:26:52,583
Godspeed, Tomoki.

1557
01:26:52,666 --> 01:26:54,958
It's all up to you now.

1558
01:26:59,708 --> 01:27:01,083
Master!

1559
01:27:06,208 --> 01:27:08,208
Aegis power mode!

1560
01:27:14,083 --> 01:27:15,458
Dummy.

1561
01:27:15,541 --> 01:27:17,791
Why the heck were you just
going to throw in the towel?

1562
01:27:18,166 --> 01:27:20,166
I'm gonna save Hiyori
and the rest of us,

1563
01:27:20,250 --> 01:27:21,916
so don't go wussing out.

1564
01:27:22,958 --> 01:27:24,291
Right.

1565
01:27:26,291 --> 01:27:29,375
Hiyori, I know Sorami's
been changing lately,

1566
01:27:29,458 --> 01:27:31,416
but don't let it bum you out.

1567
01:27:31,500 --> 01:27:33,000
There.
You see?

1568
01:27:33,083 --> 01:27:34,583
That spot you love so much.

1569
01:27:34,666 --> 01:27:36,458
That we both love so much.

1570
01:27:36,541 --> 01:27:38,416
It's just fine.

1571
01:27:39,500 --> 01:27:41,500
Oh, right.
I forgot.

1572
01:27:42,375 --> 01:27:44,541
Here.
These belong to you.

1573
01:27:52,291 --> 01:27:54,125
They look good on you.

1574
01:27:54,208 --> 01:27:56,250
I've always thought so.

1575
01:28:00,041 --> 01:28:01,291
I--

1576
01:28:01,875 --> 01:28:03,333
I remember you.

1577
01:28:03,416 --> 01:28:05,125
Huh?

1578
01:28:05,208 --> 01:28:06,958
Tomoki.

1579
01:28:09,125 --> 01:28:10,500
Hiyori!

1580
01:28:11,666 --> 01:28:13,541
It's time for you to go.

1581
01:28:13,625 --> 01:28:15,875
If you stay any
longer the explosion

1582
01:28:15,958 --> 01:28:18,000
is going to destroy you both!

1583
01:28:18,708 --> 01:28:20,750
I know you can hear me, Ikaros.

1584
01:28:20,833 --> 01:28:22,083
And you were right.

1585
01:28:22,166 --> 01:28:24,458
We are the same.

1586
01:28:24,541 --> 01:28:25,750
We don't want--

1587
01:28:25,833 --> 01:28:27,875
--the boy we love to die.

1588
01:28:27,958 --> 01:28:29,666
I can't stop the process now.

1589
01:28:29,750 --> 01:28:32,500
But there's one
final thing I can do!

1590
01:28:32,583 --> 01:28:35,291
Commencing program hack.

1591
01:28:43,041 --> 01:28:45,458
Lowering Aegis.

1592
01:28:45,541 --> 01:28:47,083
Master!

1593
01:28:47,875 --> 01:28:49,333
Tomoki.

1594
01:28:49,916 --> 01:28:51,375
Thank you.

1595
01:28:52,125 --> 01:28:55,541
I'm sure you've long since
forgotten but the reason

1596
01:28:55,625 --> 01:29:00,666
I came to love Sorami so
much was because of you.

1597
01:29:01,208 --> 01:29:03,291
Here...
I found these!

1598
01:29:04,416 --> 01:29:06,208
Thanks a lot.

1599
01:29:06,291 --> 01:29:09,333
Now that you've got 'em back,
you don't have to cry.

1600
01:29:09,416 --> 01:29:10,375
Hey, come here!

1601
01:29:10,458 --> 01:29:12,458
Wanna see something cool?

1602
01:29:14,041 --> 01:29:15,583
Heh.
It's neat, huh!

1603
01:29:15,666 --> 01:29:16,375
Yeah!

1604
01:29:16,458 --> 01:29:17,458
Isn't it pretty?

1605
01:29:17,541 --> 01:29:18,625
Uh-huh!

1606
01:29:19,791 --> 01:29:22,833
Those bells in
your hair look pretty, too.

1607
01:29:23,500 --> 01:29:25,208
Hey, you wanna play with me?

1608
01:29:25,291 --> 01:29:28,125
It's way more fun than
being all alone, right?

1609
01:29:29,375 --> 01:29:30,583
Yeah!

1610
01:29:32,125 --> 01:29:35,708
At that moment, I decided
to live in your town forever.

1611
01:29:35,791 --> 01:29:39,000
To find my bliss
in an endless dream.

1612
01:29:39,500 --> 01:29:41,333
We didn't have
much time together,

1613
01:29:41,416 --> 01:29:44,166
but getting to know all
of you, especially you,

1614
01:29:44,250 --> 01:29:47,750
Tomoki, brought me
such happiness.

1615
01:29:48,125 --> 01:29:49,458
Hiyori!

1616
01:29:49,541 --> 01:29:51,541
Thank you for being my friends.

1617
01:29:51,625 --> 01:29:53,916
I had the time of my life.

1618
01:29:54,000 --> 01:29:57,208
And Tomoki,
I really do love you.

1619
01:29:57,291 --> 01:30:00,041
Hiyori!
Don't go!

1620
01:30:22,416 --> 01:30:24,458
I swore to her, Ikaros.

1621
01:30:24,541 --> 01:30:28,166
I swore to Hiyori
that I was gonna save her!

1622
01:30:39,416 --> 01:30:41,125
And now she's gone!

1623
01:30:42,166 --> 01:30:45,791
I know that I'll
never forget her.

1624
01:30:48,125 --> 01:30:53,083
You were the first girl who
ever told me that she loves me.

1625
01:30:53,541 --> 01:30:56,000
Thank you, Hiyori.

1626
01:31:07,416 --> 01:31:12,375
♪ closing song ♪

